\begin{center}
  \begin{tabular}{NlN}
   \toprule
        \text{Probability} &  Of & \text{Value} \\
   \midrule 
   p & \text{Drawing a single} & \frac{1}{2} \\
   & \text{defective bulb} & \\
    \midrule 
    q & \text{Drawing a single} & \frac{1}{2} \\
    & \text{non-defective bulb} & \\
    \bottomrule
  \end{tabular}
\end{center}



The probability distribution of drawing $N$ defective bulbs $(0\leq N\leq 4)$ is therefore 

 \begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{NNNNN}
      \toprule
      P_0 & P_1 & P_2 & P_3 & P_4 \\
      \midrule
      \frac{16}{81} & \frac{32}{81} & \frac{8}{27} & \frac{8}{81} & \frac{1}{81} \\
      \bottomrule
      \end{tabular}
\end{center}
